 Compile a test fixture annotated with Lombok, preferably `@Value` plus `@Builder`.\n3. At runtime assert generated API behavior (e.g., `Person.builder().name(...).build().getName()`).\n4. Also use `ServiceLoader<Processor>` to obtain Lombok’s registered annotation processor and assert its supported annotation types. This is a natural public SPI entry point and constructs `AnnotationProcessorHider$AnnotationProcessor`, which creates the shadow-loaded core processor.\n\nThe processor’s constructor reaches `Main.getShadowClassLoader()`, then loads `lombok.core.AnnotationProcessor` through `ShadowClassLoader`.\n\n### Call-site mapping\n\n| Call site | Normal route | Plan |\n|---|---|---|\n| `loadClass:542` `findLoadedClass` | Every shadow-loader class request, including construction of the core processor | Covered by `ServiceLoader<Processor>` construction and compilation. |\n| `loadClass:559` `super.loadClass` | Resolution/delegation for JDK classes required by shadow-loaded Lombok classes | Covered naturally while defining/initializing the core processor. |\n| `getResource_:510` `super.getResource(altName)` | A non-shadow/JDK dependency lookup attempts SCL alternate resource first | Covered naturally during delegated JDK dependency resolution. |\n| `getResource_:514` `super.getResource(name)` | Same delegated lookup’s normal resource fallback | Covered naturally. |\n| `getResources:459` `super.getResources(name)` | `SpiLoadUtil` discovers Lombok Javac handlers/visitors via `META-INF/services/...` during processor initialization | Reached by compile-time annotation processing of the Lombok fixture. |\n| `urlToDefineClass:614` `findLoadedClass` | Only after `defineClass` throws `LinkageError`, a defensive duplicate-definition/highlander recovery path | Leave unreached. It requires duplicate/conflicting class definition across loader contexts and is not a normal supported application path. |\n| `getResources:466` `super.getResources(altName)` | Only when callers enumerate a `.class` resource through the internal shadow loader | Leave unreached. No supported public Lombok API exposes the internal loader for this request; reflection/custom loader access would violate test constraints. |\n| `getResourceSkippingSelf:527`, `:531` | Only when `shadow.override.lombok` is configured and override lookup falls back while skipping Lombok’s own shadow JAR | Leave unreached. It requires a development override classpath containing normal Lombok class files; packaged Lombok supplies shadowed resources, and a temp/custom loading fixture would be unsuitable for Native Image. |\n\n### Concrete follow-up test shape\n\n- Replace the placeholder with one public dedicated class:\n  `src/test/java/org_projectlombok/lombok/ShadowClassLoaderTest.java`.\n- Keep it outside `lombok.*`.\n- Add a nested Lombok fixture such as:\n  - `@Value`\n  - `@Builder`\n  - fields `String name`, `int age`\n- Test generated builder/getter/equality behavior without version-specific assertions.\n- Add a test using `ServiceLoader.load(Processor.class)` that instantiates the Lombok processor and verifies it advertises Lombok annotation support. This drives the runtime shadow-loader path without direct reflection.\n- Update `build.gradle` only to add the annotation-processor dependency described in preflight.\n\nThis provides supported compile-time Lombok behavior plus the runtime loader construction path, while avoiding the internal override, duplicate-definition, and custom-loader scenarios that cannot be safely represented in Native Image.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06514fc50ee21b66016a4b8076a72c8191aeb6b48c5de73678\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-codex-responses", "provider": "openai-codex", "model": "gpt-5.6-terra", "usage": {"input": 2678, "output": 3194, "cacheRead": 51712, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57584, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1783332937531, "responseId": "resp_06514fc50ee21b66016a4b804a2ae08191bea194ee4cbb4bee"}, "toolResults": []}
